Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta electrodes were fabricated via electrophoretic deposition (EPD).
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: Multi-layers of the anode layer, a buffer layer, a cathode layer, and an electrolyte layer were successively deposited on a graphite rod via EPD.
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: A single cell can be obtained via a one-step co-firing processing.
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The stability of the slurries can be controlled by changing the amount of phosphate ester (PE), which is added as a charging agent.
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the slurry increased with increasing PE, while the pH decreased.
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The deposition rate and thickness of the deposited layers increased with the applied voltage and deposition time.
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition

Sentencas: The fabricated symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell, with the configuration of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (SFM-GDC) anode/Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta buffer//LSGM electrolyte//Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta buffer/Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (SFM-GDC) cathode, showed a maximum power density of 116 mW/cm(2) at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication of an La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte-based symmetrical microtubular SOFC single cell with Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ electrodes via electrophoretic deposition
